House Resolution 860
By: Representatives Martin of the 49th and Jones of the 47th
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Marie Lewis Garrett; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
3 with the passing of Marie Lewis Garrett on August 10, 2024; and
4 WHEREAS, Marie Lewis Garrett was born on October 20, 1953, on Governors Island, New
5 York, a beloved daughter of Russell and Maria Lewis; and
6 WHEREAS, she was immensely proud of her father's distinguished military service,
7 honoring his memory by laying wreaths at Arlington National Cemetery, and she deeply
8 cherished her mother's Austrian heritage, maintaining close ties with her European relatives
9 and speaking fluent German; and
10 WHEREAS, a dedicated public servant, Marie Lewis Garrett earned her undergraduate
11 degree from the University of Georgia and received a Master of Science from Georgia State
12 University's College of Public and Urban Affairs in 1985; and
13 WHEREAS, she began her distinguished public service career with the City of Alpharetta,
14 Georgia, where she served from 1982 to 1993 in multiple leadership roles, including Director
