15 of Planning and Community Development from February 1982 to May 1989, Assistant City
16 Administrator from May 1989 to May 1991, and City Administrator for Development from
17 May 1991 to March 1993; and
18 WHEREAS, she later played a pivotal role in the planning and development of numerous
19 municipalities throughout metro Atlanta, serving as the first City Manager of Brookhaven,
20 Georgia, from December 2012 to January 2016 and consulting for the cities of Powder
21 Springs, Stone Mountain, Roswell, Dunwoody, and Sandy Springs through her firm, Marie
22 Garrett Consulting Inc.; and
23 WHEREAS, throughout her career, she held key roles such as Special Advisor to the Mayor
24 of Canton, Interim City Manager for Johns Creek, Consultant for the City of Milton, and
25 Vice President of Development at Harry's Farmers Market Inc., where she handled
26 governmental affairs and legislative lobbying at the federal, state, and local levels; and
27 WHEREAS, she was united in love and marriage to her husband of 46 years, Steve, and was
28 blessed with three remarkable sons, Stephen, Zachary, and Matthew, and three cherished
29 grandchildren, Rachael, Grady, and Julia, who knew her affectionately as "Oma."
30 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
31 the members of this body join in honoring the life and memory of Marie Lewis Garrett and
32 express their deepest and most sincere regret at her passing.
33 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
34 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
35 family of Marie Lewis Garrett.
